#FEATURE EXTRACTION USING PCA

from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
from time import time

ncomponents = 50
nsamples=449
height=224
width =224
t0 = time()
principle_components = PCA(n_components=ncomponents, svd_solver='randomized',
          whiten=True).fit(X_train)
print(" this is done in %0.3fs" % (time() - t0))

print("we are taking out our top %d eigenfaces from the given %d cases"
      % (ncomponents, X_train.shape[0]))

 this is done in 1.998s
we are taking out our top 50 eigenfaces from the given 449 cases

#FINDING BEST ESTIMATORS WITH GridSearchCV AND APPLYING SVM 
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.svm import SVC


print("wea re Fitting the classifier to our training set")
t_0 = time()
parameter_grid = {'C': [1, 10, 100,1e3, 5e4, 1e4],
              'gamma': [0.005, 0.001, 0.1, 0.01], }
my_classifier = GridSearchCV(
    SVC(kernel='rbf', class_weight='balanced'), parameter_grid
)
my_classifier = my_classifier.fit(X_train_principle_components, y_train)
print("Best of the estimator that was found by our grid search for our model is:")
print(my_classifier.best_estimator_)
print("this is done in %0.3fs" % (time() - t_0))
